column11: The data you carry is vital to the remaining Federation fleet. You'll need supplies for the journey, so make sure to explore each sector before moving on to the next. But get to the exit before the pursuing Rebel fleet can catch up!  TIP: Grinding Sectors -  It can be beneficial to stay in a Sector for as long as possible to improve the ship since each Sector is increasingly difficult.
You approach cautiously but you detect no danger. It appears to have been a small rest stop that was abandoned a while ago. You take what few supplies you can find.
Now that their ship has been emptied of hostiles, you search it. Eventually you find a prisoner who offers to join your crew.
Thank you! If you can just give us a count on their numbers perhaps we can get the Rebels to help. Added a quest marker to your map!
There are no more life-signs remaining on the ship. You strip it of useful materials.
With the patrol ship taken care of you hasten to leave. It won't be long before the other ships catch up.
A transmission from the nearby planet indicates an outpost below which offers supplies to travelers. You send down an away party to check it out.

column11: With your teleporter damaged and no way to fix it, you take one of the enemy ship's shuttles to return to your own ship.
Your abandoned crewmember is waiting on the ship when you return, trying not to dwell on the fate of his previous incarnation.
If the reports are true, this area has been under the control of pirates for quite some time. Some traders still attempt to trade with the few settlements that remain, but they do so at great risk.
Take this bit of scrap as a down-payment. We'll use your jump signatures to follow you. You're really helping us out here. Added a quest marker to your map!
